    "<strong>Evening:</strong> use the softer light for photography and give yourself time for a quiet sundowner before returning to camp.",
  ]},
  { type: 'h2', content: 'Culture, Community and Conservation' },
  { type: 'text', content: "The wider Samburu region is home to Samburu communities whose pastoral traditions, beadwork, songs, cattle culture, and land knowledge are deeply connected to the landscape. A respectful cultural visit can add real depth when it is arranged through community-led channels and framed as exchange rather than performance." },
  { type: 'text', content: "Northern Kenya is also one of the strongest examples of community conservation in Africa. Conservancies around Samburu help protect migration corridors, support ranger programs, and create tourism revenue that can benefit local people directly. For travelers, that means the safari can contribute to a broader living landscape rather than only a fenced park experience." },
  { type: 'image', src: '/images/maasai-cultural-experience-safari_blog.jpg', alt: 'East African cultural experience with traditional dress and beadwork', caption: "Cultural encounters are strongest when they are community-led, respectful, and given enough time." },
  { type: 'h2', content: 'When To Visit Samburu' },
  { type: 'text', content: "June to October is classic dry season. Wildlife concentrates more predictably near water, roads are usually easier, and the spare beauty of the landscape feels especially powerful. January to March is another excellent window, often hot but rewarding, with clear skies and strong wildlife viewing." },
  { type: 'text', content: "November and December can bring short rains, fresh grass, dramatic skies, and excellent birding. April and May are usually the wettest months; they can be beautiful and quiet, but some routes require flexibility. For photographers, the shoulder seasons can be magic if you are comfortable trading predictability for atmosphere." },
  { type: 'h2', content: 'How Samburu Fits Into a Kenya Safari' },
  { type: 'text', content: "Samburu pairs naturally with <strong>Ol Pejeta Conservancy</strong>, where rhino conservation and chimpanzee sanctuary visits add a different kind of wildlife story. From there, travelers can continue to <strong>Lake Naivasha</strong> for water, birds, and a softer lakeside pause before finishing in the <strong>Maasai Mara</strong> for big-cat country." },
  { type: 'text', content: "That progression works beautifully for honeymooners because it feels varied without becoming frantic: northern rarity, conservation depth, lakeside calm, then the classic Mara finale. Families also enjoy it when the pace is carefully managed, with enough pool time, lodge comfort, and shorter drive expectations built in." },
  { type: 'image', src: '/images/itin-kenya-honeymoon.jpg', alt: 'Kenya honeymoon safari itinerary preview', caption: "Samburu is a natural opening chapter for a varied Kenya honeymoon safari." },
  { type: 'h2', content: 'Final Thoughts' },
